values:
Just to pop into live journal and give the other side of the world the news... 

We got married on 8/25/07 

5 hours later - we got pregnant! 

YAHOOO! 

A baby is on the way! 

Due middle of May. 

I am 7 weeks along, no the math doesn't work. but if you know anything about pregnancy you'll know they date from the your period not conception. 

Sounds screwy, when you know you've only be pregnant for 5 weeks, but they say 7.

Personality cocktail
From Go-Quiz.com
Refiner's fire, my hearts one desire is to be holy. Set apart for you, my love, ready to do your will.
and i miss him. even more annoying.

You are SpongeBob SquarePants: You are the classic person that everyone loves. You
are the best friend anyone could ever want to
have and never want to lose. You never cause
harm to anyone and they would never not
understand your feelings. Life is a journey
it's funny and calm for the most part. Stay
away from traitors and jealous people & then
you will be stress free.

Which cartoon describes your personality?
brought to you by Quizilla I have decided that if i ever i stop thinking that my best friend is no longer the bestest best friend in the entire world, than they are no longer my best friend. It clicked today. & I like it. Oh I couldn't resist, I mean Spongebob? really...
I am employed again!! Children's Ministry Administrative Assistant!!!
She was born on Sunday, July 24th to some very dear friends of mine. She is beautiful!!!

Indeed, that very night, the impossible had already been set in motion.

I saw a movie by myself for the very first time ever!

I'll take ONE ticket for 7:40 showing of Charlie and the Choclate Factory...

Everything in this room is *eat*able. In fact, I'm *eat*able. But that is called cannibalism which is frowned upon in many countries.

Have you ever actually seen a real live yellow duck?

Draw me close to you
Never let me go
I lay it all down again
To hear you say that I'm your friend
You are my desire
No one else will do
Cause nothing else can take your place
To feel the warmth of your embrace
Help me find the way
Bring me back to you

You're all I want
You're all I've ever needed
You're all I want
Help me know you are near

It's like they just switch up the words a little bit. And could it be rain with out clouds? And really how often do the clouds really come with out rain. Since its going to be cloudy with rain somedays, does that mean the showers come with out the clouds? 

Its good to know weather in the northwest is back to normal and this girl is back to wearing her chacos. Nothing like being able to puddle jump at a moment's notice!
It's snowing! It's snowing! It's snowing!
I am not superwoman. I do not want to be independent.

Ive been feeling kind of restless
Ive been feeling out of place
I can hear a distant singing
A song that I cant write
And it echoes of what Im always trying to say

Theres a feeling I cant capture
Its always just a prayer away
I want to know the ending
Things hoped for but not seen
But I guess thats the point of hoping anyway

Of going home, Ill meet you at the table
Going home, Ill meet you in the air
And you are never too young to think about it
Oh, I cannot wait to be home

Im confined by my senses
To really know what you are like
You are more than I can fathom
And more than I can guess
And more than I can see with you in sight

But I have felt you with my spirit
I have felt you fill this room
And this is just an invitation
Just a sample of the whole
And I cannot wait to be going home

Going home, Ill meet you at the table
Going home, Ill meet you in the air
And you are never too young to think about it
Oh, I cannot wait to be going, to be going home

Face to face, how can it be
Face to face, how can it be
Face to face, how can it be

Cuz this is just an invitation
Just a sample of the whole
And I cannot wait to be going home

Amazing Grace, how sweet the sound,    
That saved a wretch like me....
I once was lost but now am found,
Was blind, but now, I see.

T'was Grace that taught...
my heart to fear.
And Grace, my fears relieved.
How precious did that Grace appear...
the hour I first believed.

Through many dangers, toils and snares...
we have already come.
T'was Grace that brought us safe thus far...
and Grace will lead us home.

When we've been here ten thousand years...
bright shining as the sun.
We've no less days to sing God's praise...
then when we've first begun.

Amazing Grace, how sweet the sound,    
That saved a wretch like me....
I once was lost but now am found,
Was blind, but now, I see.

I think that I must always have an extra room available in my future homes. Not that my sailors don't do just fine on the couch, however, each time they come more stuff lingers... & I think I need an extra room just for thier stuff.
I am getting my new car today! Yahoo!

"I will send you a volunteer crew application.  We always hire Canadians as crew since we have so many capable people to choose from.  For that reason, we have not needed to look outside of Canada."


Guess I'll just have to make sure someone starts their own USA organization that I could crew on someday...

I miss someone terribly tonight. Just someone. 
Time for bed. 
Because that is where old boring people go when they feel blah. 
bleh.

would you?
would you just call me crazy?
I'm officially now the "puppet" for my 5 year olds every sunday morning. I am stoked. Very much so.
This morning I am tired. I want to crawl back in bed so bad... so bad. Bleh!

New job. New car. New life. New outlook. Same God.

I am an adult. Yes, at 24 I am. Finally, almost, barely made it? Yes, maybe. 

I had a wonderful experience with my brother. Not necessarily good. & I am not so happy that he didn't leave me a note telling me where he was at tonight... 

However I am exhausted & need to go to bed & be anxious for nothing.

The wooden boat festival was an absolute blast. I love boats and the ocean & know I will sail someday. & someday soon. 

Friends are good, they are grand. Even, & sometimes especially the ones that don't love Jesus because He is there working in theirs hearts. 

God is awesomely good. 

I am working on not doing some things I shouldn't be doing. & be honest about what I have been doing. God is creating an amazing conviction in my heart.

I have a new job. 
I start October 4th.
I am getting a new "used" car. 
My family loves me and is helping me...
more than I could imagine or ask for. 
I don't deserve any of it. 

I wanna cry I am so happy and joyful. 
Just not bouncy to add to it.
so far to go, so much to learn. So many ways to grow. I like me. I do.
and today I am going to hear about that job!

I have 24 hour non-stop access to an instaneous healer of all wounds.

Yesterday I was sad. Depressed. Melancholy. Whatever words you wish to use. Maybe just being a silly girl. 

But over night a magical confidence was placed in my heart, an understanding, a peace, yes a peace that transcends all understanding and overwhelming joy. 

I believe we were created to be happy creatures. Full of joy and love. & that's how I feel today. 

I LOVE JESUS!
They (the new job people) are checking my references....
What would you do if every time you wanted someone they would never be there?

Possible new job in the works. They are checking my references. Ready to walk away from current job big time. 

God... give me grace to accept unorganized people and corporations. please. allow me to accept your grace and show it.

When did i become so content with being with me? Currently looking forward to a bubble bath, candles, and my bible followed up by a few movies while curled on the couch in my pajamas with the possibilty of some craftiness... and very much looking forward to the evening. Am aware that plans may change as they so often can do and that I am not in control, oh though how very much I like to think so.

My car is ready to blow

My checking account is absolute mess

I have to have a new job by the middle of October

& school starts soon

All of this should add up to a huge anxious mess...

Am I apathetic or at peace?

I feel a peace but it could just be a huge piece of apathy pie. I guess we'll find out eventually. I'm good, no great actually. Just not to an extreme. Full of joy from the love of Jesus Christ and slowly recovering from past wounds. off to my bath now...

Praise for challenges that build character!

Now off to my bath!

 "EVERYTHING! Everything that you wanted I have done. You asked that child be taken. I took him. You cowered before me and I was frightening. I have reordered time. I have turned the world upside down. AND I HAVE DONE IT ALL FOR YOU! I am exhausted from living up to your expectations. Isn't that generous? "

so my student loan was approved. I can't really believe it. I guess I just assumed something would probably fall through at the last minute. Have enough $ to cover tuition and books with my student loan... so we shall see... I'm excited and scared to death... Good thing I have a big God!

it's not all over at 24 right? I got until at least 33... or so I've been told. 

It's going to be a quiet birthday... that's been awhile. But should be interesting enough...  this be my first sober birthday since sometime around the age of 14 or 15 I'd say.
I've come along way from 23 to 24... it's been an amazing journey. I couldn't be more thankful to the people I have had by my side. Thank you!

I've got routines for when he's here, routines for when he's gone, Routines for when he's here and I have to pretend he's not. Pick up the mail, scan for important stuff, get it ready to send off, make note of what needs to be paid and when. Remember that storage unit gets paid 1st of the month. Remember to keep us up on cc payments and such and such. Interesting, how easily it was to click right back into it. Maybe I never clicked out. I like it. It seems to be part of who I am. Anyhow, My God is so great, so strong and so mighty there's nothing my God can not do! I miss my church and my kids.... only one more sunday without them...
I had a friends of ours tonight say the following words  "I've been thinking about the church thing" How awesome is that? God is so good!

Home:

  1. A place where one lives; a residence.
  2. The physical structure within which one lives, such as a house or apartment.
  3. A dwelling place together with the family or social unit that occupies it; a household.
  4. The place, such as a country or town, where one was born or has lived for a long period.
  5. The place where something is discovered, founded, developed, or promoted; a source.
  6. A headquarters; a home base.

I am home. At headquarters. Where I live. It doesn't feel like home. It feels temporary. Or like time's almost up. Who knows. I am tempted to start the application process for Multnomah in the spring. I don't think I want to wait two years for it. More prayer, but what is this desire I have in my heart. What is it?? Lord, It's bigger than I am. This dream & I can't keep it down. If it's you it will come to pass, maybe next year, maybe in ten, maybe in fifty. Thank you, Lord!

I just had a wonderful nine days, on the road away from here. Away from Bellingham, but not away from what felt like home. Maybe I just consider this base camp for the time being. Who knows.

Just looked at $$$ spent on the trip. It was fun, it was worth every penny. Next time I'll know where we can crunch the dollars, but no use looking back and thinking OUCH that cost us a bunch. I had the time of a lilfetime & so did he.

Off to new starts. New beginnings. Figuring out school and a new job. ASAP. I need a new job. ASAP. Maybe the right one is out there waiting for me. I feel like I need to really really get my life in order. Like I am preparing for something. Something big is coming soon. Not real soon, but soon. And if my God is telling me to get my butt in line for it then so be it...

I love Jesus!!
THANK YOU AND GOODNIGHT RACH-I-POO, IGA PRESIDENT. "I'M NOT JUST THE PRESIDENT, I'M A MEMBER TOO" CORKY SUPERGIRL HAYS

Leo July 22 - August 22  You're going to get it all today, dear Leo. You may not be feeling especially powerful, and in fact, there may be those around you trying to make you feel incompetent. Realize that this is simply a passing trend and that you will soon bounce back to your true lion self. Open your aperture up a little more than usual and let more light into your life. You'll shoot some of the best shots on the roll today.

Sometimes I think Jesus might have a hand in these ol'horoscopes. Don't remember the last time I read mine, but this one was right on the money. :)

good to eh to bad to crap to whatever... whatever. I give. 

sure I understand it's all good. like always.
